ygData.subject: Popularity with Rivervalers
ygData.msgSnippet: Greetings, Thanks for the advice, perhaps I ll tough it out until I m a little higher in level.  But the lack of cash is killing me! I have no clue what I did
ygData.messageBody:
Greetings,

Thanks for the advice, perhaps I'll tough it out until I'm a little
higher in level. But the lack of cash is killing me!

I have no clue what I did to give me the faction rating I have. I
entered Rivervale as a lowly level 2. I hunted a bit in Faydark, then
traveled to Freeport ... hunted a tiny bit there but lag prevented me
from getting anything good really. I did manage to get to level 2 and
get Discord. And then I made the trek to Rivervale. Perhaps it's the
deity I chose? I can't remember which one I chose (although I usually
chose the nicest sounding one, lol ... I love Tunare and will chose her
if I have the choice). When I arrived I conned "apprehensive" to every
npc but the innkeeper who conned disinterested but he won't sell or buy
from me anyways.

I've been killing bixies and those little goblin guys ... workers or
something like that ... anyways, they're very similar to those annoying
green men that roam everfrost. lol

Oh, and btw, I'm a SHE not a he. <g> I had to chuckle at the couple
posts that referenced me as a "he" or a "him". ;-) I'm the cute little
redheaded woodelf running around Rivervale (Quellious) in the *very*
skimpy bathing suit the EQ developers dressed me in.

Safe travels,
Wynsong
Woodelf Bard, Level 3 (and a half! ;-)
Rivervale, Quellious
